-- BBC to Introduce iPlayer Globally as Apple iPad Application, FT Reports
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-12-02T06:37:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/bbc-to-introduce-iplayer-globally-as-ipad-application-ft-says.html
The British Broadcasting Corp. plans
to introduce an international version of its iPlayer video-on-
demand service as an application of Apple Inc.’s iPad, the
Financial Times reported, citing  Luke Bradley-Jones , the
managing director of BBC.com, the BBC’s commercial web arm.  The U.S. is likely to be the first market in which the
application will be available, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alan Purkiss  in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in London at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 